For awhile I use to be embarrassed of the moments in my life that weren’t the brightest. I looked down upon the moments I struggled, and the period where I battled addiction. For years I shunned the bad things that happened and tried to pretend it didn’t exist. A year ago I learned to embrace these moments and realized my “battle scars” led me to where I am now. Those dark moments are the reason I’m the person I am today. Everything happens for a reason.. don’t let this platform fool you it’s just a bunch of ppl posting their highlights. Your life matters and whatever you’re dealing with at this very moment is doing nothing more then.. creating armory for tomorrow! 🫶🏼

2023 for me was a year of self improvement, constant self reflection, counting my blessings while separating the lessons. Realizing what wasn’t “meant for me” was never meant to be. I’ve reached new heights physically and learned the sky is truly the limit. Anything is possible with belief in yourself, and a strong mindset. My biggest takeaway was mental and emotional growth. I’ve learned that my worth isn’t based on the perception of others but solely based on how I perceive myself. I’ve learned self love is the most important form of love. It’s truly the only love you need. I became my own peace and I promised myself I would never invest more than what was invested in me. 2023 wasn’t an “ IG perfect story”.. it was filled with many lows but the HIGHS kept me going. It may sound cliche but I know the best version of myself is entering 2024 and ready to have the BEST YEAR YET. Cheers to closed chapters, new beginning’s and teaching me sometimes there are indeed…BLESSINGS in disguise 🙏🏼✨

-therealalexg 🫶🏼
